00:22:30.839 --> 00:22:36.079
For others, he provided a way to think about understanding our subconscious, a way

00:22:36.079 --> 00:22:41.629
to try to understand who we really are, a way to explain our thoughts and feelings.

00:22:42.669 --> 00:22:47.749
Whatever side of the argument you come down on, it’s undeniable that he has left a

00:22:47.829 --> 00:22:53.809
huge mark on how we think about thought, how we think at how all of our minds work.

00:22:54.909 --> 00:22:58.909
He might not have been right about everything, and he certainly made mistakes,

00:22:58.989 --> 00:23:05.529
but as he famously said, “from error to error, one discovers the entire truth.”

